Thank you for choosing ManaStorm Studios ("we", "us", or "our"). We are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our applications, websites, and games (collectively, the "Services").
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. By accessing or using our Services, you agree to be bound by the terms and conditions described herein and all terms incorporated by reference. If you do not agree to all of the terms set forth in this Privacy Policy, you may not access or use the Services.
1. Collection of Information
We collect several types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Services to you:
1.1 Personal Data
We may collect personal information from you directly when you use our Services, register for an account, make a purchase, or communicate with us. This information may include but is not limited to:
Name
Email address
Age and gender
Country, city
Any other information you choose to provide
1.2 Usage Data
We automatically collect information when you access or use our Services. This information may include:
IP address and unique mobile device identification number (e.g., device ID, advertising ID, MAC address)
Device information (for example, device type, operating system, language, time zone)
Game data (for example, consumer’s account, game progress, and in-game event logs)
Purchase history (for example, consumer’s purchase ID, amount spent, currency, time of purchase)
Other data provided to us by the browser.
1.3 Cookies and Tracking Technologies
We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our Services and hold certain information. You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you do not accept cookies, you may not be able to use some portions of our Services.
1.4 Data from Third Parties
We may receive additional data about you if you choose to connect third-party services with our Service:
Data we receive if you link a third-party tool (such as Facebook, Apple or Google)
Demographic data (such as to determine the coarse location of your IP address)
Data to fight fraud (such as refund abuse in games or click fraud in advertising)
Data from platforms that the games run on (such as to verify payment)
Data for advertising and analytics purposes
2. Use of Information
We may use the information we collect for various purposes, including:
Providing, maintaining, and improving our Services
Communicating with you and responding to your inquiries
Customizing your experience and delivering relevant content
Processing transactions and fulfilling orders
Protecting against fraud and unauthorized transactions
Complying with legal obligations
Sending promotional communications, if you have opted in to receive them
Monitoring and preventing any problems with our Services
Ensuring fair gameplay and enforcing our acceptable use policy
3. Disclosure of Information
We may disclose personal information we collect or consumers provide:
Contractors, service providers and other third parties we use to support our business
To advertising partners, with your consent, for marketing purposes
In some cases, if law enforcement agencies comply with reasonable legal requirements, we may need to provide consumers’ personal information
If we or our subsidiaries are involved in a merger, acquisition or asset sale, consumers’ personal information may be transferred
To our subsidiaries and affiliated companies
When we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property or safety of the company, our customers or others.
4. Data Transfer
Your information, including Personal Data, may be transferred to — and maintained on — computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ from those in your jurisdiction.
By agreeing to this Privacy Policy, you consent to this transfer. We will take all reasonable measures to ensure that your data is treated securely and in accordance with this Privacy Policy.
5. Data Retention
We will retain your Personal Data only for as long as is necessary for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. We will retain and use your information to the extent necessary to comply with our legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our policies.
6. Data Security
The security of your data is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Data, we cannot guarantee its absolute security.
7. Your Data Protection Rights
We aim to take reasonable steps to allow consumers to correct, amend, delete or restrict the use of personal data.
Consumers can modify their logged-in personal information at any time, or request us to delete the personal information we have collected. However, the aforementioned requests to delete or modify information may prevent us from providing normal games or related services. In this case, our company will Please note in advance that if consumers still request to delete or modify information, the company has the right to terminate all related services without assuming any liability for compensation.
Under the GDPR regulations, should you wish for your data to be deleted, please send out a request to
Account Deletion
page:
Please note that before responding to such requests, we may require identity verification to ensure that the data belongs to the consumer.
8. Third-Party Services
Our Services may contain links to third-party websites, applications, and services. We are not responsible for the privacy practices or content of these third parties. We encourage you to read the privacy policies of any third-party sites or services you visit.
We may use third-party Service Providers to monitor and analyze the use of our Services, display advertisements, or provide certain features. These third parties have access to your Personal Data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.
9. Children's Privacy
Our Services are not intended for children under the age of 18.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18.
If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so that we can delete the information.
10. Links to other websites
Our Service may contain links to other websites. We are not responsible for the content of other websites and consumers are advised to read the privacy policies of other websites before submitting any personal information to them.
11. Changes to this Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.
You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.
12. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at admin@manastorm.tech.
By using our Services, you acknowledge that you have read and understand this Privacy Policy and agree to be bound by its terms and conditions.
